track.name: Bring It on Home
comments: Perfection ♫ ♥ ♥ ♥ ♫
Led Zeppelin robbed this fantastic song. And they did not make any change from the original version.
+++Klasse+++
Growing up in Arkansas, my dear Mother trusted me (after teaching how operate the record player) with her music....Been shaped ever since
this may be the baddest blues piece in here
Wow . SONNY BOY ! - Forever !!!
Fun music! I feel blessed to be able to finally be able to listen to good old blues

I first heard this song over 6 years ago and but somehow it's not jumped into my mind that I also own the Led Zep version of the song (and that such a version exists) until just know. My mind is slightly blown.
oh my soul
Nope, it's Sonny Boy. Wolf's delivery is a lot gruffer... but besides that I know it's Sonny.
For some reason, it says Sonny Boy Williamson, yet I seem to be hearing Howlin' Wolf, "Evil"...?
blues at there best
roll me a fat one and pass that bottle to me,.........
Master of maestros, salud!! Mr. Williamson. salud!!!!
One of the best :-)
theres nothing to say about. the song speaks for itselfs.
Where would Clapton, Zep etc be without classics like this!
Hier is Kurt. Sonder 'n helm en sonder 'n veiligheidsgordel.
hammer
BRING IT ON HOME SONNY !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
